<topic id='attribute_death_location_type_code.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: DEATH LOCATION TYPE CODE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
The type of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_location">LOCATION</xref>:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
At which a 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>
 died or                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
The preferred 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_location">LOCATION</xref>
 of death of the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>, as stated by the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>, 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_patient_proxy">Patient Proxy</xref>
 or 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_carer">Carer</xref>.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
Note that 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATIONS</xref>
 may choose to collect the 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_death_location_type_code">DEATH LOCATION TYPE CODE</xref>
 codes at the high level (National Codes ending in "0") or at the more detailed level below each high-level code.        </p>
  </div>
</body>
